post_text: DCS Families and Community, our food service staff had a very busy summer...and they're ready to kick off the new school year. See the attached for information about our meal plans. All kids ages 0-18 eat for free. This includes our children who are not old enough to attend school, our home schooled students (not enrolled in DCS), our remote students, and our hybrid students. Tomorrow, Friday, 9/11, meals can be picked up at the elementary cafe door near the pool between 11-1. Students who are fully remote, not enrolled, or who won't be on campus Monday are welcome to pick up their meals tomorrow. We hope to see you there!

post_text:
Deposit CSD has been provided a cancer prevention grant from the Broome County Health Department. With this grant, we're looking to promote sun safety. So far, we've been able to purchase two shade structures that will be used at the pool and on the front lawn of the high school. It's been a hot and sunny summer. We're asking our followers to help us promote sun safety by messaging a picture of yourself wearing sunscreen, hats, sunglasses, or just chilling in the shade. We'll share any pictures we get during the first week of school. You can learn more about sun safety here: https://takeactionagainstcancer.com/
#sunsafeselfie
Broome County Health Department

post_text: DCS Families, as usual, you do not need to worry about spending money on supplies for school. If your family has chosen the hybrid program and will be on campus during the week, we will have the supplies your child needs - including face masks. If you have chosen the remote option (this applies to hybrid, too) your child will have the technology he/she needs to be successful. Of course, you are allowed to provide your own masks for school, but we will have enough to keep all of our students safe. We'll be publishing dates for our parent Q & A meetings early next week. Have a wonderful weekend.

post_text:
DCS Families, the governor announced today that schools are allowed to host in-person learning on the school campus this fall. This does not change our plans, but allows us to move forward with our plans for both hybrid and fully remote learning. If you did not get a call last week to discuss your choice of learning programs for fall, please call the main offices next week. We still have a lot of planning to finalize in order to be ready for September. We're working on some informational videos for you and we'll be hosting some question and answer sessions in the near future (dates to come soon). Don't forget to visit our school reopening web page for more information and contact the building principal with any questions.
https://www.depositcsd.org/SchoolReopening2020.aspx

post_text: DCS Community, the parade and fireworks are on for tonight!! Come out to celebrate our seniors. Parade begins at 7:30. The route is: Pine Street to Division. Division to Front. Front to Court. Court to Second. Second back to school. Seniors: Please be at the school and ready to line up at 7 PM. Line up begins at the bus garage. Seniors can also stop at Honey's Cafe after the parade for a free ice cream! Fireworks start time range: 9:15-9:30. Fireworks will be deployed from the same location as the Lumberjack Fest fireworks. Enjoy!!

post_text: DCS Seniors and Parents of Seniors: Today the governor announced that outdoor, socially-distanced graduations of up to 150 people will be allowed beginning June 26th. This would move us into plan B. We are waiting to see the exact language of the completed executive order before more details are released. Once we have some specific information, we'll reach out to you with the details. Each day a new adventure! Thanks for giving us a little time to sort it out.

Students, are you looking for summer employment? If so, please consider contacting the Delaware County CDO Workforce at the number below to apply!

Summer Employment:
Are you between 14-20 and looking for a summer job? We have a program for you! Delaware County is currently accepting applications for youth ages 14-20 for the Summer Youth Employment Program. This program offers summer jobs and paid educational opportunities for kids right in their own communities. Your safety is important to us! Protective equipment and additional supervisory staff will be provided to keep everyone as safe as possible. Remember it’s the early birds that get the worms so apply today! Please call 607-832-5782 for your application to be emailed or mailed out.

post_text: DCS families, the governor has officially closed school throughout the remainder of the academic year (June 2020). We are heartbroken. We will wait for more guidance regarding the possibility of hosting an in-person event for graduation. Principals will communicate with parents and students about end of the year procedures (locker clean-out; materials etc) in the near future. While our buildings are not open to students, school is still in session. Our remote learning plan remains in effect. We hope that you are all well and know that we're thinking about you all the time!

Good afternoon,

We are excited to share some awesome news!!!
We have determined the Valedictorian and Salutatorian for the Deposit Central School District’s Graduating Class of 2020! 😃

Both of these girls have worked tremendously hard throughout their years at Deposit, and these recognitions are well-deserved! 👏🎉👩‍🎓👩🏻‍🎓📚👍

Congratulations to Mikayla M., our Valedictorian!
Mikayla is planning to attend the University of Buffalo in the fall, majoring in Pre-Med.

Congratulations to Kambria R., our Salutatorian!
Kambria plans to attend the Pennsylvania College of Technology in the fall, majoring in Architecture.

Congratulations, Mikayla and Kambria!!
We cannot wait to see the amazing adventures that lie ahead of you and all that you will surely accomplish!￼ 💛
￼
We are so proud of all of our students at Deposit!! #LumberjackStrong

post_text:
DCS Families,
As you may have heard, Broome County announced that all schools are mandated to be closed until April 13th. It is my understanding that Delaware County will be making an announcement in the very near future. Our district is unique in that we occupy both Broome and Delaware counties. Many of our students, however, attend Broome County educational programs. Before I make a final statement about closure, I am waiting to hear from Delaware County. I will be attending an emergency meeting at the county tomorrow morning. Once I have done that and have had a chance to meet with the administrative team, I will communicate more information to staff and families. Right now, I appreciate your patience as we gather more information and make plans to address everyone's needs. I will post updated information by tomorrow. - Denise Cook, Superintendent

post_text: Our elementary students were treated to visit from author and illustrator Ross Burach! They learned how to create a story and illustrations and even had the opportunity to create some of their own! Ross Burach loves drawing pictures, making up jokes, dabbling in animation, and hanging out with his family. He is the author and illustrator of There's a Giraffe in My Soup, The Very Impatient Caterpillar, and I Am Not a Chair, as well as the illustrator of Jennifer Hamburg's Billy Bloo Is Stuck in Goo, hailed by Publishers Weekly as a "high-energy cartoon that looks as though it sprang directly from a child's imagination." Ross lives in Brooklyn, New York.

post_text: Deposit CSD is thankful for our veterans! Do you know a veteran of the US armed forces who wasn't able to receive a high school diploma because he/she was busy serving our country? Our school district would be honored to offer a high school diploma to any veterans who may have served our country in during WWII, the Korean Conflict, the Vietnam War, or any veteran who served active duty. It is not necessary that the veteran attended high school in New York State, but he/she must be a current New York State resident. Veterans who received a high school equivalency are eligible as are next of kin to deceased veterans. Please contact the office of the superintendent if you would like more information. 607-467-5380

post_text: Congratulations to the DH Lady Eagles Basketball team for advancing to the MAC Championship game. The game will be played on Friday, 2/21 at the Binghamton University Events Center. Tip-Off will be at 6:00. Admission will be $5.00 for adults, $2.00 for Seniors and Students, Kids 10 and Under will be free. Good luck ladies!!!

post_text:
Our new Junior/Senior Student Honors Lounge opened today! This idea began in Mrs. Wehrli’s College Writing class, as a persuasive writing idea. After months of research, fund-raising, and hard work, we celebrated this morning with a ribbon-cutting ceremony.
Students are eligible to enjoy the lounge during study halls, lunch, or advisory if they are Juniors in Honor Society, Seniors in Honor Society, Members of Tri-M Music, or Seniors with teacher mentor recommendations.
Special thanks to Mrs. Sanford for sharing her space and time, Mrs. Wehrli for assisting with planning and preparations, the Senior Class for donating a coffee machine, and Mr. Matthews for building our dividers and assembling furniture!!
Special thanks and congratulations to Senior Class members Rylie Lang, Madison Stanton, Mikayla Martin, and Evie Davis, who spent endless hours working to see this through to fruition!!! We are so proud of what our students accomplish when they work together!!! 👏💛👍
